{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncResult","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Asynchronous operations are broken up into two separate operations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which are chained together by a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":". To begin","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"an asynchronous operation, provide a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":" to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous function. This callback will be triggered when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operation has completed, and must be run in a later iteration of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the thread-default main context (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"]) from where the operation was"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"initiated. It will be passed a "},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance filled with the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"details of the operation’s success or failure, the object the asynchronous","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function was started for and any error codes returned. The asynchronous"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback function is then expected to call the corresponding ","type":"text"},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function, passing the object the function was called for, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance, and (optionally) an "},{"code":"error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to grab any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error conditions that may have occurred."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function for an operation takes the generic result","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and returns the specific result that the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operation in question yields (e.g. a [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/FileEnumerator"},{"text":"] for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“enumerate children” operation). If the result or error status of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operation is not needed, there is no need to call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function; GIO will take care of cleaning up the result and error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information after the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"type":"text","text":" returns. You can pass"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":" if you don’t need to take any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action at all after the operation completes. Applications may also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"take a reference to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" and call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" later;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"however, the "},{"code":"_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function may be called at most once."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Example of a typical asynchronous operation flow:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["void _theoretical_frobnitz_async (Theoretical         *t,","                                  GCancellable        *c,","                                  GAsyncReadyCallback  cb,","                                  gpointer             u);","","gboolean _theoretical_frobnitz_finish (Theoretical   *t,","                                       GAsyncResult  *res,","                                       GError       **e);","","static void","frobnitz_result_func (GObject      *source_object,","\t\t GAsyncResult *res,","\t\t gpointer      user_data)","{","  gboolean success = FALSE;","","  success = _theoretical_frobnitz_finish (source_object, res, NULL);","","  if (success)","    g_printf (\"Hurray!\\n\");","  else","    g_printf (\"Uh oh!\\n\");","","  ...","","}","","int main (int argc, void *argv[])","{","   ...","","   _theoretical_frobnitz_async (theoretical_data,","                                NULL,","                                frobnitz_result_func,","                                NULL);","","   ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback for an asynchronous operation is called only once, and is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"always called, even in the case of a cancelled operation. On cancellation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the result is a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_IO_ERROR_CANCELLED"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"I\/O Priority","anchor":"IO-Priority"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many I\/O-related asynchronous operations have a priority parameter,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"which is used in certain cases to determine the order in which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operations are executed. They are not used to determine system-wide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"I\/O scheduling. Priorities are integers, with lower numbers indicating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"higher priority. It is recommended to choose priorities between"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_PRIORITY_LOW"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_PRIORITY_HIGH"},{"text":", with ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_PRIORITY_DEFAULT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as a default.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResultRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncResult","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"name":"Note"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncResult"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a base class for implementing asynchronous function results."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","title":"AsyncResult","externalID":"s:3GIO11AsyncResultC","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncResult","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AsyncResult"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/asyncresult"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(_:)-1eqij","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(_:)-4tg0e","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(_:)-5nb16","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(_:)-7bkon","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(_:)-7uob1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(raw:)-5fm5t","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(raw:)-5qt5k","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init(retainingRaw:)-9jevr","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncResult\/init